="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>就绝对数字而言，2023 年再次击败了《美国的早晨》。就最近的变化而言，就更难说了。 1984 年，通货膨胀率从几年前接近 15% 的高峰值回落，但最近略有反弹。 2023 年，通胀有所下降，但下降是最近的事——就在去年。所以哪一个看起来更好取决于你选择的参考点。</p><p>买房怎么样？从<a href="https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/HSN1F">原始数据</a>来看，现在的单户住宅销售量与 1984 年的水平大致相同。当你根据人口进行调整时，2023 年的销售额占黄金年龄（25-54 岁）人口的百分比略低于 1984 年——目前每 1000 人 5.45 %，而 1984 年每 1000 人约 7 %： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe3908457-466c-456a-bcc9-ba08642a295b_1318x450.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe3908457-466c-456a-bcc9-ba08642a295b_1318x450.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe3908457-466c-456a-bcc9-ba08642a295b_1318x450.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe3908457-466c-456a-bcc9-ba08642a295b_1318x450.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe3908457-466c-456a-bcc9-ba08642a295b_1318x450.png" width="1318" height="450" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/e3908457-466c-456a-bcc9-ba08642a295b_1318x450.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;im