"9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：<a href="https://twitter.com/vebaccount/status/1685470963511508992">亚历克斯·威廉姆斯</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>对某些人来说，这些图表的含义是，最近的经济扩张在某种意义上终于治愈了 2008 年的创伤。这里的叙述是，我们在大衰退期间没有采取足够的财政刺激措施，这对我们的经济造成了永久性损害，我们最终通过在大流行期间和之后花费了大量资金来弥补。</p><p>但尽管我确实认为我们应该在大衰退期间采取更多刺激措施，但大流行支出治愈了我们经济的观点似乎非常可疑。正如<a href="https://twitter.com/arpitrage/status/1686013157708300294">经济学家阿皮特·古普塔（Arpit Gupta</a> ）和其他人指出的那样，只有当你忘记考虑通货膨胀时，煎锅图才看起来像煎锅。 Mike Konczal 按实际值重新绘制了图表，发现它们看起来根本不像煎锅： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae93b34b-4d5b-4754-8f5f-79b215b537c0_900x900.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae93b34b-4d5b-4754-8f5f-79b215b537c0_900x900.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae93b34b-4d5b-4754-8f5f-79b215b537c0_900x900.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae93b34b-4d5b-4754-8f5f-79b215b537c0_900x900.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae93b34b-4d5b-4754-8f5f-79b215b537c0_900x900.jpeg" width="900" height="900" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/ae93b34b-4d5b-4754-8